I haven't looked at all the posts above, it is pretty clear looking at wallet listing code how 
Lutz's first character bug could arise when `wallet_dir` ends in a slash. It looks like this bug was introduced in ed2e18398b3ab657e98e3e1fe135cbf8dd94fda3 and could probably be fixed by:

```diff
diff --git a/src/wallet/db.cpp b/src/wallet/db.cpp
index cd49baeb786..191e15c494a 100644
--- a/src/wallet/db.cpp
+++ b/src/wallet/db.cpp
@@ -12,7 +12,7 @@
 
 std::vector<fs::path> ListDatabases(const fs::path& wallet_dir)
 {
-    const size_t offset = wallet_dir.string().size() + 1;
+    const size_t offset = wallet_dir.string().size() + (wallet_dir.has_filename() ? 1 : 0);
     std::vector<fs::path> paths;
     boost::system::error_code ec;
 
```
